  <body>
	<%= partial(:navigation) %>

	 <div class="intro">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="row-fluid">
                <div class="span6">
                    <img src="images/taneth-1500.jpg" width="100%" />
                </div>
                <div class="span6">
                    <h1>Greetings</h1>
                    <p class="lead">Welcome to NineCollective's MineCraft headquarters! Here, you can connect NineCollective players, browse our growing library of blueprints, or checkout our company map.</p>
                    <div class="row-fluid">
                        <div class="span12">
                            <form class="well">
                            <p>Wanna help on our Reddit PVE project?</p>
                            <div class="input-append">
                                <input type="email" class="" name="email" placeholder="Your Email please..." />
                                <button type="submit" class="btn">Sign Up</button>
                            </div>
                            </form>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

	
    <div class="container main">

      <h1>Welcome to Taneth</h1>
      <p>This is the build guide for the awesome mega-build Taneth on the Reddit PVE Server.</p>
	  <h2>Taneth History</h2>
	  <p>All Taneth Lore still needs to be fleshed out</p>

	  <br/>
	  
	  <h2>Task List</h2>
	  
	  <ol>
		<li>Get on Mumble!</li>
		<li>Find Location for Castle - Ideally a Hills Biome so we can put castle on Hill</li>
		<li>Build Mine Entrance and Storage/Smelting Room</li>
		<li>Layout Castle Foundation using Stone Bricks</li>
		<li>Figure Rough plan for roads and bridges out of main castle</li>
		<li>Start laying out Farms</li>
		<li>Once Castle is done - layout plots for buildings in the city</li>
	  </ol>
	  
	  <h3>Texture Pack</h3>
	  <p>For the most part we are all using <a href="http://bdcraft.net">Sphax PureBDCraft</a> You should Get it NOW!</p>
	  <p>Note: We are also using the textures from Sphax PureBDCraft on this site in our blueprints, that's how much we love this texture pack.</p>
